<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
In addition to characters in the genus description, the species is characterized by the following primary and secondary male sexual characters. Sternite VIII without apical incision. Tergite X apparently fused to internal face of lateral sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5A</figureCitation>
, solid line), with two large setae situated at apical third of length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5A</figureCitation>
; LS). Sternite IX emarginate apically, with symmetrical basal stem (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5A</figureCitation>
, dashed line). Lateral tergal sclerites and tergite X of approximately equal length. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5B, C</figureCitation>
); paramere longer than and closely attached to, median lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5B</figureCitation>
); lateral apical area of paramere with setae of varying length (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5C</figureCitation>
; ST); internal sac consisting of a pair of heavily sclerotized oblong-shaped sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5C</figureCitation>
; OS) and pair of weakly sclerotised longer, more slender sclerites extruding from apical area of median lobe under pressure (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Morphology of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. A male terminalia (abdominal segments IX, X) B aedeagus in lateral view C aedeagus in antiparameral view (slightly lateral). LS, Long setae. OS, Oblong sclerite. SS, Slender sclerite. ST, setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372640" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">5C</figureCitation>
, SS).
</paragraph>
