<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="103" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="103">
Based on the specimens studied here, the new genus is restricted to the lowland areas of the Amazonian basin of Peru (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Known distribution of Amazonothops aslaki gen. et sp. nov. in Peru." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.904.48592.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/372641" pageId="0" pageNumber="103">6</figureCitation>
). As a fully winged species known only from six specimens from two areas approximately 1000 kilometres apart from each other, it seems to be a widespread species, perhaps much more than it appears now.
</paragraph>
